ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC SCOREACCEL SESSREF=session-name | SESSUUID="session-uuid"; 
    PUBLISHMODEL required-arguments <publish-model-options>; 
    RUNMODEL required-arguments <run-model-options>; 
    DELETEMODEL required-arguments <delete-model-options>; 

PROC SCOREACCEL provides an interface to the CAS server for DATA step and DS2 model publishing 
and scoring. 

Models can be published and executed in CAS, or in an external database: 
  o DATA step and DS2 model code can be published to a CAS table and executed in CAS 
  o Model code can be published from CAS to an external database and then executed there via the 
    SAS Embedded Process (EP). Teradata and Hadoop are supported.
